===Etymology===
Unknown. The phrase was used as early as 1906 (in Canada) with the usage being neither disparaging nor better than non-government work.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=MxEyAQAAMAAJ&pg=PR245&dq=%22good+enough+for+government+work%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCYQ6AEwAGoVChMIoZ_ph8GuyAIVyxg-Ch0gswbf#v=onepage&q=%22good%20enough%20for%20government%20work%22&f=false]</ref>. It was used disparagingly as early as 1960<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=pmt68RIT0t4C&q=%22good+enough+for+government+work%22&dq=%22good+enough+for+government+work%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0CCYQ6AEwAGoVChMIysCpiMOuyAIVi5UeCh1TMw6B]</ref>.

